  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency help for the locally hired staff of the Embassy of Finland in Kathmandu affected by the earthquake</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The big earthquake in Nepal on the 25th of April 2015 is estimated to affect into the lives of several millions of people. Some of these Nepalese people who lost their homes and belongings work at the Embassy of Finland in Kathmandu. This amount (max. 15 0
00 euros) will be used for immediate needs and first stages of reconstruction.   The purpose of this emergency help for the locally hired staff of the Embassy of Finland in Kathmandu is to help people to be able to rebuild their homes and continue their li
ves after the earthquake. The Embassy&apos;s main task in Nepal is development co-operation. For the continuity of the Embassy&apos;s operations it is critically important that these employees are able to continue their work at the embassy.</narrative>
  </description>
